        {
            "title": "美伊停火後霍爾木茲海峽通行前景不明 仍有逾800艘船隻滯留",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit max-w-full\"><img alt=\"来源： 彭博\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"696\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/KZTTEBdKMgGR9e7sl8Xqpg--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTY5Ng--/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/b7163f148ec222e78ee1bd188c0eef0c\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\">来源： 彭博</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><br/></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 周三霍爾木茲海峽仍大體處於受阻狀態。在美國與伊朗達成一項脆弱的停火協議後，船東正試圖評估能否安全地通過這一關鍵水道。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">彭博匯編的船舶追蹤數據顯示，周三僅有三艘船隻駛離該地區。其中部分與伊朗有關聯，而伊朗媒體隨後報導稱，在以色列對黎巴嫩發動襲擊後，海峽的油輪通行已受阻。正常情況下，每天約有135艘船隻通過，目前有超過800艘貨船滯留在海灣內，大多等待離開。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">儘管船東和保險機構紛紛對停火表示歡迎，但同時警告稱，還需要更多細節來判斷是否可以安全通行。伊朗表示，停火的一個先決條件是其武裝部隊應負責協調通過霍爾木茲海峽的船隻。德黑蘭還對部分船隻收取高達每次200萬美元的通行費。</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-d5e8ff5b-22fc-394f-bc46-3b63db0c614d-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">「時間將證明這是停火暫歇還是和平降臨，但就目前而言，通往海灣地區的貿易極不可能就此恢復，」Lloyd’s Market Association海事與航空負責人Neil Roberts表示。</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit max-w-full\"><img alt=\"來源： 彭博\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"696\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/7y6fyXk94NhCBrmNulXITg--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTY5Ng--/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/e05360416d2b7277a5305dab1170f68d\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\">來源： 彭博</figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題Hormuz Stays Blocked for Now as Hundreds of Ships Seek Exit (2)</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">--聯合報導 Stephen Stapczynski、Dan Murtaugh、Tsuyoshi Inajima.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-yga='{\"yLinkElement\":\"context_link\",\"yModuleName\":\"content-canvas\",\"yLinkText\":\"bloomberg.com\"}' data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2026 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
